               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-6v: Prayer, “For the sake of peaceful holy things,”Bä’ǝntä Qǝdsat, በእንተ፡ ቅድሳት፡ ሰላማዊት፡. MQ 26 –9; MG 41ff.; Liturgy 33 –7. F<locus target="#6v"/> and passim, mention the owner, ኃይለ ሥላሴ. F<locus target="#6v"/>-8v: Prayer, በሰማይ የሀሉ ልብክሙ,  from the Anaphora of Our Lord. F<locus target="#8v"/>-17v: Prayer, እግዚአብሔር ዘብርሃናት. F<locus target="#17v"/>-19v: Prayer, ፍትሐተ ማይ. F<locus target="#19v"/>-34r: Prayer, ነአኵተከ አምላክ ቅዱስ, from the Anaphora of Our Lord with the remainder of the Anaphora. F<locus target="#34r"/>-39v: Prayer, Praise of the Beloved for Mary, from Horologium for the Night Hours.  F<locus target="#40r"/>-42v: Prayer, Praise of the Beloved for Mary and her Son Together. F<locus target="#45r"/>-66r: Chants called Kǝśtät, ክሥተት፡.  Arranged for the days of the week: Wednesday (<locus target="#54v"/>), Thursday (<locus target="#57v"/>), Friday (<locus target="#59r"/>),  Saturday (<locus target="#60r"/>). F<locus target="#67r"/>-72v: Asmat prayer spoken to Andrew, EMIP 247. Incipit: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ . . . ጸሎት፡ ዘተናገሮ፡ ለእንደርያስ፡ ሐዋርያ፡ ጸሎቱ፡ . . .  <locus target="#72v"/> mentions the scribe, ኃይለ ማርያም. <locus target="#75r"/> has a pen trail in form of a prayer, "Bless my pen; make it a good writing pen."</summary>
